rk%20for%20ITER%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20a%20tokamak%2C%20a%20large%20device%20with%20metal%20ladders%20and%20scaffolding%20around%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663948fe10dfcda40967459a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22552%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20WEST%20tokamak%20has%20a%20volume%20of%20about%20530%20cubic%20feet%2C%20making%20it%20medium-sized%20compared%20to%20ITER.%3Cp%3ECEA%2FC.%20Roux%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWEST%20has%20a%20lot%20in%20common%20with%20ITER%2C%20a%20nearby%20reactor%20being%20built%20in%20southern%20France%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhich%20will%20be%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-the-iter-nuclear-fusion-plant-and-why-is-it-important-2016-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20largest%20tokamak%3C%2Fa%3E%20capable%20of%20self-sustaining%20burning%20plasmas%20when%20it's%20finished.%20Creating%20that%20self-heating%20mix%20is%20a%20crucial%20step%20to%20harnessing%20the%20power%20of%20fusion%20for%20commercial%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20due%20to%20cost%20and%20technology%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2023-01-international-fusion-energy-delays-chief.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esetbacks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20unclear%20when%20ITER%20will%20be%20finished.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20other%20facilities%20are%20conducting%20experiments%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20best%20to%20operate%20the%20giant%20reactor.%20That%20includes%20WEST.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20reactors%20are%20practically%20neighbors%2C%20and%20the%20experiments%20at%20WEST%20are%20directly%20applicable%20to%20ITER%2C%20Delgado-Aparicio%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20fusion%20to%20happen%20on%20Earth%2C%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efuel%20needs%20to%20reach%20at%20least%2050%20million%20degrees%20Celsius.%20One%20of%20the%20main%20obstacles%20fusion%20power%20faces%20is%20that%20it%20takes%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20energy%20to%20generate%20those%20extreme%20temperatures%2C%20and%2C%20so%20far%2C%20reactors%20can't%20sustain%20a%20plasma%20long%20enough%20to%20gain%20an%20energy%20surplus%20that%20could%20be%20put%20toward%20commercial%20use.%20For%20now%2C%20fusion%20reactors%20typically%20consume%20more%20energy%20than%20they%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWEST's%20latest%20breakthrough%20was%20no%20exception.%20However%2C%20it%20did%20generate%2015%25%20more%20energy%20from%20fusion%20compared%20to%20earlier%20attempts%2C%20PPPL%20reported%20in%20a%20statement.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20plasma%20was%20twice%20as%20dense%2C%20another%20important%20component%20of%20creating%20more%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20key%20to%20WEST's%20record%20success%3A%20tungsten%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20holds%20a%20sample%20of%20tungsten%20in%20a%20glass%20jar%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66394aac10dfcda409674605%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETungsten%20is%20a%20heavy%20metal%20that%20WEST%20uses%20in%20its%20tokamak%20because%20of%20its%20heat-resistant%20properties.%3Cp%3EJulian%20Stratenschulte%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWEST%20is%20helping%20scientists%20test%20the%20best%20materials%20for%20building%20the%20walls%20inside%20a%20fusion%20reactor%2C%20which%20isn't%20easy%20since%20these%20environments%20can%20reach%20temperatures%20more%20than%20three%20times%20hotter%20than%20the%20sun's%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%2C%20WEST%20contained%20carbon%20walls.%20While%20carbon%20is%20easy%20to%20work%20with%2C%20Delgado-Aparicio%20said%2C%20it%20also%20absorbs%20tritium%2C%20a%20rare%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foppenheimer-science-to-understand-physics-ato